Sentencas: Lowering operating temperature and optimizing electrolyte thickness, while maintaining the same high efficiencies are the main considerations in fabricating solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, the effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrical performance was investigated.
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte was coated on the nickel-samarium-doped composite anode/ samarium-doped ceria electrolyte substrate with varying bilayer electrolyte thicknesses (1.5, 3.5, 5.5, and 7.5 mu m) via dip-coating technique.
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance analysis revealed that the bilayer electrolyte with 5.5 mu m thickness exhibited high open circuit voltage, current and power densities of 1.068 V, 259.5 mA/cm(2) and 86 mW/cm(2), respectively at 600 degrees C. Moreover, electrochemical impedance spectroscopy analysis also exhibited low total polarization resistance (4.64 omega cm(2)) at 600 degrees C for the single SOFC with 5.5 mu m thick yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These findings confirm that the yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte contributes to oxygen reduction reaction and successfully blocks electronic conduction in Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study has successfully produced an Y0.25Bi0.75O1.5/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 bilayer system with an extremely low total polarization resistance for low-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Effect of yttrium-stabilized bismuth bilayer electrolyte thickness on the electrochemical performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
